## PB3(3/5): stack-local `Signal(T)` is rejected in V1.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 29 (PB3 design checkpoint): Signal owns a
## `Vec(*Closure())` of retained subscribers. The Vec is a
## resource value type that requires an M20e-style scope-exit
## defer-guard to release the buffer at scope exit. Wiring
## Signal through the same `resourceKindOfBinding ->
## .vec_value` machinery as Vec is possible but bigger than
## the smallest-safe-path rejection.
##
## All canonical PB2 / PB3 / canary uses of Signal are
## heap-owned via `*Signal(T)` — `*` makes the allocation
## visible AND wires Signal's `__rig_drop` through M20h's
## `hasRigDrop` hook so the subs-Vec destructor fires on
## last-strong drop. The diagnostic points the user at the
## fix.

sub main()
  sig: Signal(Int) = Signal(value: 0)
